{"questionId":"22224695","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>It is given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>10</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence, find the values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> for which <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is increasing.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;(accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≥</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22224695","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ2.8aii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, find the values of x for which f is increasing.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.2—Increasing and decreasing functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
